caption: Late night drinks and snacks! A little pricey, but worth it. The bar was nice, drinks good and outside seating as well. This was my first time going. I will be back. Nice bar to go to if you love Sports. TVs everywhere. I loved it!
The inexperienced waitress was taking to long to come check on us each time she left.
Went to lunch on 3/24/2021 it was the worst, we could not eat the food. Please don't go for lunch, you will be very disappoint.

Yesterday, I didn’t know I was in for a little treat, but I had the best server and such a great time with my family. Jesse was our server. He’s was so fast, intentive to our needs and just overall one of the best server I ever had. The food was surprisingly really tasty. I order a watermelon margaritas and Cajun chicken pasta. The pasta was full of flavor.My family enjoy their food to. I will definitely be back soon.
Good drinks great price

I went twice actually, and had very sub par experiences here. The first time everything was fine , great service at the bar. Until i got my food. I ordered the prime burger .. but it was missing the prime rib meat.. it had two slices, complete false advertisement in comparison to the picture. I ate half my burger before the manager brought me some. I wasnt bothered until she hesitantly handed me the "extra" meat she was bringing me. holding it in front of me, explaining how people believe it should be more meat because of the picture, and how it should only be 3 oz. A portion... when she never even saw what I originally received and tried to argue with me .. I almost told her I didn't want it anymore, but took it to not be rude..  my second experience the food was better, no complaints, except my server kept forgetting what we ordered and came back several times for us to remind her. Sometimes I felt she completely forgot about us.. despite the experiences I'll probably return just because the food was decent for the price. So I guess it's TRUE. You get what you pay for.
Excellent bartenders, and food is very tasty. Definitely try the wind zingers (garlic parmesan).

SPEND YOUR MONEY SOMEWHERE ELSE! Trust me, take this as a warning.  Oh wow. Where to even start? I was so excited about visiting this place. But that excitement quickly fizzled. We waited 45 minutes only to be told that our name was accidentally taken off of the waiting list by their system. But then when we got int, they said our number had been already called and that we missed our table. Once we were finally seated, we had lemon water and then nothing for 30 minutes while waiting on the server to serve. The food was just okay. Very basic for the price. Will not be going back.
The food and drinks were great. Nice portion size too.
Very nice
Food was great and service! Wait on seating, to be expected (30mins). Will repeat. Made my birthday dinner night.

“Classic hamburger” had no taste it was very dry, the service was very bad, the waitress barely even came to check on the table and didn’t gave us silver ware. Philly steak also dry no flavor at all, I wasted almost $70 for bad food wouldn’t go back at all. Calamari was just plain. Drinks were so bad mojito very bad no flavor and margaritas.
Took us in last minute off of road trip. Great management ,and staff ! excellent steak
The host Giovanna was very hospitable and our server help us to decide on what to try.  The wingettes could have used a little salt and pepper.   Will be back!!!  Thanks lady
The food was great. The service was great.  The prices are great. Family friendly restaurant. Big enough to be seated safely inside. seating.

I will tell you that Miller's Ale House was an excellent experience especially waitress "Ms. Jazzy" whom was and excellent representative of "Miller". The drinks are price are very reasonable with a touch if class. Ruby Tuesday and Friday's watch out you have some competition in the area.  The onsite Manager if the day very pleasant and very professional. I would recommend Miller's Ale House to anyone that wants a great meal at great prices $$$$$$$.
Mmm mmm mmm. Great freaking drinks! The food was on point. They were short staffed literally 2 people Terika and Wade the manager. They did well. Will be back!!
Very nice, bartender is nice, the beer taste rich, my wings was great, watching my ballgame, my new chill spot

i love this place.  the wait is long starting at around 6:00 pm, i think... if you get there soon after 5 you'll have no problem getting in. and if you show up late and dont get a table, just stick around and they will still seat you at the end of business hours for a late (but absolutely delicious) dinner...

Been eating here shortly after it opened and in the beginning everything was great, every item ordered was delicious and fresh. Then a decline began, its natural as restaurants move forward, but then I ordered from here and got food poisoning. I can't be sure it was from here specifically, but It made me wary to order again. Tonight all I wanted was a pretzel and remembered they had one on the menu so decided to take a chance, well delivery comes, everything is meh on quality and of course pretzel was missing, so the only reason I tried again was for that item left out. Place has been moving in the wrong direction and now I'm moving on as well.
Fresh tasty burgers!
Friendly,fast ,with great dining options thats why Millers ale is a great place to dine either with family or grabbing a quick bite.
Love this new spot ,went for my birthday n had a blast. Area is very clean, tV's everywhere u will not miss a game . Love the menu n bar will go back at anytime.
Good drinks, decent food, reasonably price. Quincy is the BEST bartender, his customer service was great
This place is just great. Great prices, great service, great food, and great drinks! Service was great by Terika made me the best mojito
All I can say is great
Great craft beer selection and good food bargains. You will not be disappointed in any aspect, Tyler's an awesome bartender with great personality.
Food was ok but the service was much better I can say then the food but I had a good time the 1 time
Always good
Great experience!!  Jazzy was great and I will ask for her by name the next time we stop in.  I didn't have to chase her down for service and she checked on us several times. She did a great job👏🔥💯👍
Wonderful place for share with friends or family. I had the pleasure to taste The Salmon and an Ice cream dessert, congrats to the chef. Good parking lots, nice location, excellent team.
Great management, food and  atmosphere 😊
Jazzy was the best waitress, the food was excellent & the service was the bomb.com
Can not wait to go in and have a cocktail and appetizers.
I simply love their food. I always get excellent customer service there. The place is well organised and the cashiers are always very friendly. Will come visit again.
Food customer service was excellent
Amazing staff great food fantastic environment.
I ordered two burgers well done and they came medium rare and some really pink in the middle. The raspberry lemonades were wonderful.
Terika was a delight. good prices
Exciting since my Washington Team was playing! Awesome experience! Good food too! Please add a lil more sugar to the not so sweet tea! Lol! Thanks Dewan for great service! You rock!
1st time there, was getting ready to close
Those Korean Chicken Strips are the bomb dot com!
The staff was friendly and the food was great.It was my first time there I had the chicken and steak combo fajitas.

My family loves Miller’s Ale House we eat there at least two times a week since opening day!!!! They have the “Best Managers” Mr Andre and Ms Marsha they put Service in Customer Service!!! The servers are are great!!!! The ice cream is the best!!!
Tasty food. Good value.

This was my first time dining at this location but my friend suggested it.  I think the cobb salad is the best I have ever had in LIFE.  I was extremely disappointed in Simone.   She decided to charge us for a shot at the bar and we were gifted one by other patrons nearby.  She did this simultaneously.  I questioned the charges and she said we ordered one so she charged us for the one we ordered.  But she never asked us if we still wanted to purchase an additional shot?  My friend covered the bill and said not to worry but in the future this will NEVER occur.  I felt that was very sneaky.  I will return again but I will keep a closer eye on the tab.
Everything was good!!!
So far everything I've eaten from this place has been great service has been great
Funny,   enjoy good. Food,,  learn that u SHOULD. Ask to get wings cook. Crisp...........
It was my first time there and i will definitely be going back. The food was great, drinks were nice and the customer service was fantastic. They really took care of us.

This is my second time using delivery for this restaurant. The food is very good,  but I wish the chefs would avoid using some much salt. Both times my food was way too salty. Next time I order I hope I remember to advise to go easy on the salt. Otherwise, I would have given it five stars  The donuts are delicious. Please add to the delivery menu!!! The manager made an exception and sent me some
The waiter was very nice and the food was good
Great customer service and food. I just hope they don't comfortable and change. Sometimes that happens when a new restaurant get established. Don't change Miller Ale House
Great service I love it how they had bilingual host at the door
EVERYTHING
Lots of different beers and great daily specials

Overall great experience. Service was good. We went on a Sunday night so it was pretty busy. Some things were a bit too salty, but we enjoyed our meals for the most part. Affordable. Will visit again.

Went to Miller's with a friend for lunch today.  My 1st time there. We were seated in a timely manner.   Our bartender/server Rush was great.  I ordered their lunch fish with French fries.  It was very good. However,  I did not receive any ketchup for the fries and the amount of tartar since that was served made me think that it was the last in the container.   My friend ordered the zinger lasagne.  She thought the lasagne was a bit chewy but the zingers were good.  I will definitely will be going back to try other dishes.

This location has only been open a month..The staff were great. All the food came out fresh, and hot. The two bartenders  Shay and T are on their A game. I think my wife and I found a new hangout spot.
Great Place to eat.
Friendly service good food and outdoor televisions 👍
This is my second visit, it was very nice. The food was fresh and good. The staff very friendly.
You feel like family being here because the service and atmosphere are that good. The food, BEST wings outside of the NWPA/Buffalo area!!  Post stickers, Ribs, kids meals, also really good.

The food and the service is.the bomb.com! Chris, Pavi,  Josh, Rush, Simone, Brina, Tyler, Erin and Que customer service is excellent 👌 and Thank you! They all deserve a raise! I have been there 3 days in a row (total 10.visits since they open) Coming back tomorrow for the prime rib 😊
Wonderful restaurant/bar. Great decor and delicious food. Reasonably priced. Our waiter Erin provided exceptional service and he made us laugh. Erin is definitely a huge asset to your company.
Food is good but SUUUUUPER SLOW service. We shouldn't be waiting 25+ mins for our water.
The food was great. There were a few people in my party and not one complaint. The people were nice and everyone's order was right. I will be going back.
Great atmosphere, Great Prices on Drinks and a awesome happy hour menu. If you need a place to wind down, go get yourself a seat, grab a drink or two, and enjoy. The staff and management are amazing.
Very friendly!
Never again. Manager didn't excuse my id even during pandemic. Won't recommend to no one
Fantastic atmosphere fantastic music fantastic staff fantastic food fantastic dessert and good drink prices. Check it out you will definitely come back.
Good selection and service.  Nice layout of the restaurant also
Nice Spot just recently opened and I don't have to drive to Rockville to get great quality service and atmosphere. I will return

(Original) Muy buen ambiente valió la pena llegar acá su atmósfera llena de vida sus bares su comida en especial las chicken & steak fajitas uffff so good, muy satisfecho mi primer día en un lugar nuevo , suerte ...
Delicious food and drink, friendly staff, great outdoor seating, and surprisingly reasonable prices for the DC area. My new favorite haunt!

To start on i went on a Friday of course everything is packed . The host said it would be a 30 mins wait , so i went to the mall and came back on time . I had to wait an additional 20-25 mins . Drinks and food price are great! Got the food my husband meat was undercooked, he order well done and for sure we got med rare , portions were small . Maybe, we will come back on day where is not busy .

I went to the new location in Hyattsville Md. for Family and Friends soft opening everything was great food drinks and staff. Tried to go back a few days later, got there and the host said it would be a 20 minute wait, cool. Gave my number went to my car to wait for the text about my table. Never received a text went back and the host said my name and number somehow got erased, so I would have to wait an additional 15-20. I was so upset and at this point extremely hungry, ended up going to another restaurant.  Really wanna come back with the family because I like the place. Is it possible to make a reservation for 5-6, because I don't wanna have this experience again.
First time trying this restaurant, food was excellent, my mom even said her sandwich was the best she’s ever had. Our server Marcus was really nice as well, I’ll be back for sure, good job!

Ron was great. His energy and humor was welcomed by our group. I was invited by a friend to join a group  to watch the Football game. While the service was GREAT and the food tasty, I was disappointed  by a few things. Our group of 10+ were enjoying celebratory shots when we were told that we had ordered too many drinks in too short a time. While I understand the responsibility of the business to monitor such things, it was a turn off to a first time guest. I assume that because my friend is a manager, no other managers came by to talk to us about the situation (I get it). She explained the situation though.... food to alcohol to time ratio. We did, however, meet Miles, Jon, Chris, TJ and Alexis... You have assembled a wonderful staff!!! I'll be back again next week! P.S. Pavi is cool!!!
Great experience, amazing staff and management. This will be definitely my go to place  to relax eat well and have fun.
Excellent experience. Friendly staff, fun atmosphere. Love the outdoor/indoor bar area. Will absolutely be back.
What a place.  so fresh so welcoming an amazing staff manager was the best great place overall. Food was 10/10 🔥

Finally! A great bar that I can walk to, the specials were amazing, I had three pitchers of miller light, a pitcher of margarita and wings for under $50. Service was fast friendly and all around a positive experience. Ill be coming back soon!

This place is very disorganized. I called ahead to see if there was outdoor seating at 6:30pm. I was told there are tables open and they do not take reservations. I arrived at 7pm and was told the max wait for a table outside was 20 minutes. I waited 45 minutes and then they tried to seat me in a table inside. The restaurant is over crowded for COVID regulations. They had 4 hosts just standing around confused when I asked about my table. I was standing right in front of them they didn't know where to find me. They never took down my number to text me when my table was ready. Another couple received several texts and their table was never ready. They are not practicing 6 feet social distance rules at the bar area. I would avoid this place. After an hour of waiting they sat a party at an outdoor table that came after me. I finally left.
(Translated by Google) Very beautiful setting with an exceptional staff. They are at your service.  (Original) Tres beau cadre avec un staff exceptionnel. Ils sont à vos petits soins.
Great customer service and delicious food!

My wife and I have been waiting for a Miller's Ale House close to our home and now we have one! They opened on my birthday! Best night spent! Food and drinks always on point! Best place to watch all games! TV'S everywhere! We definitely will be back! Thanks for the birthday dessert!
